dspace-development.title: Deliver Elements files to Digital Science via S3.

comments.body:
Given the difficulties encountered in attempting to transfer the files between the QA server environment, the FTP server, and the S3 Bucket:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/133d3b94-a594-4554-ac13-e07ede4666dc)

...an alternative proposed by @kelynch is to request to proceed with having the new `staging` environment mirror that of the `production` environment (hence, the same files and database exports could be used for both upgraded installations).
Waiting on signal sciences to verify before we delete the bucket

Digital Science confirmed we can use the production files that we have uploaded for this project both in prod and staging.  They will send us an update on their progress setting up hosted environments on Friday this week.

I am removing "delete the bucket" from this ticket and will set a reminder/make a new ticket for the end of this project as part of cleanup.
